  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  at least 3 episodes of heartburn and/or regurgitation in a week for at least 3 months.

          -  evidence for an abnormal esophagal acid exposure on impedance-pH monitoring (tested in
             the last 2 years off PPI)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  gastric or esophagal surgery

          -  active peptic ulcer disease

          -  malignancy

          -  pregnancy

          -  uncontrolled diabetes mellitus

          -  severe cardiac conditions such as cardiac arrhythmia or ischemia or cardiac
             pacemaker/defibrillator

          -  allergy to adhesives/patches

          -  severe pulmonary disease

          -  obesity (BMI&gt;30)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
